<AbstractNarration>The primary aims of the present proposed project is to study entanglement&lt;br/&gt;decoherence of many-body qubits or multilevel quantum systems and to develop a&lt;br/&gt;quantum trajectory approach in several important AMO physics domains. Two examples&lt;br/&gt;are: entanglement dynamics of multilevel atomic systems coupled to a quantized field&lt;br/&gt;and non-Markovian trajectories for quantum systems coupled to a fermionic&lt;br/&gt;environment. Our primary interest of application is quantum decoherence of quantum&lt;br/&gt;open systems in AMO and condensed matter systems and the simulation of quantum&lt;br/&gt;entanglement dynamics of many-body systems.</AbstractNarration>
